      {
        "annotationType": "ANNOTATION",
        "comment": {
          "commentType": "FUNCTION",
          "texts": [
            {
              "value": "Structure-specific nuclease with 5'-flap endonuclease and 5'-3' exonuclease activities involved in DNA replication and repair. During DNA replication, cleaves the 5'-overhanging flap structure that is generated by displacement synthesis when DNA polymerase encounters the 5'-end of a downstream Okazaki fragment. Binds the unpaired 3'-DNA end and kinks the DNA to facilitate 5' cleavage specificity. Cleaves one nucleotide into the double-stranded DNA from the junction in flap DNA, leaving a nick for ligation. Also involved in the base excision repair (BER) pathway. Acts as a genome stabilization factor that prevents flaps from equilibrating into structurs that lead to duplications and deletions. Also possesses 5'-3' exonuclease activity on nicked or gapped double-stranded DNA"
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "annotationType": "ANNOTATION",
        "comment": {
          "commentType": "SIMILARITY",
          "texts": [
            {
              "value": "Belongs to the XPG/RAD2 endonuclease family. FEN1 subfamily"
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "annotationType": "ANNOTATION",
        "comment": {
          "commentType": "SUBUNIT",
          "texts": [
            {
              "value": "Interacts with PCNA. PCNA stimulates the nuclease activity without altering cleavage specificity"
            }
          ]
        }
      },
